 "remarks": "Brook House - your retreat in North Stamford. 3 Bedroom, 3 Full baths. Front and South entrances have Stone Bridges over a calming, babbling Brook. This charming home has hardwood floors throughout adding warmth. Note the Custom tile Risers to the Second Floor. Lush property with gardens, apple and pear trees, Rose of Sharon, Japanese Maple and Mountain Laurel and the Brook. Lounge on the Flagstone, Covered Patio on the South side or the two other brick and stone patios.  On the North side is a large deck with Pizza Oven. The sizable 2-car garage is deep providing storage and work areas. The built in workman&apos;s counter, and Wood Burning stove which vents to the outside is for the DIY enthusiast. Extra Refrigerator (2-yrs old) in garage. Off the deck, in the rear of the home is a fenced-in dog run. Other things to note: Newer Breaker Box; Newer Washer/Dryer; Gasoline powered Generator; Several Skylights throughout the upper level. The 4th bedroom was used to increase the Primary Bedroom and its closet space and the closet in the 2nd Bedroom. Homeowners share Snow plowing of the road. This year&apos;s share was $231. The pictures were taken before the owner moved out. Some TLC required. You think you are choosing a house, but you are choosing a lifestyle.",
